        <hl1>THE MARKETS: CURRENCIES</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>US dollar falls against euro for first time in four days on speculation European central bank will move to support its slumping currency; chart (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>EURO RISES. The dollar fell against the euro for the first time in four days on speculation the European central bank would move to support its slumping currency. In New York, the euro rose to 89.79 cents, from 88.99 yesterday.</p>
      </block>
